<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880401-0144 </DOCNO><HL> IMF Loan to Mozambique </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AFRIC </CO><IN> MON BNK </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The International Monetary Fund authorized a $25 million loan disbursement to Mozambique. This was the second installment on an $85 million credit that the IMF approved earlier to support economic adjustments in the African country.    The IMF supervises a supply of money supported by subscriptions of member nations, for the purpose of stabilizing international exchange and promoting orderly and balanced trade. </TEXT></DOC>